{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/early-mentorship/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1350px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/422ae4c7db23fc4ac8991e74abec0f5d/b768e/photo-1518818608552-195ed130cdf4.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"photo 1518818608552 195ed130cdf4\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/422ae4c7db23fc4ac8991e74abec0f5d/b768e/photo-1518818608552-195ed130cdf4.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/422ae4c7db23fc4ac8991e74abec0f5d/20e5d/photo-1518818608552-195ed130cdf4.jpg 450w,\n/static/422ae4c7db23fc4ac8991e74abec0f5d/8e1fc/photo-1518818608552-195ed130cdf4.jpg 900w,\n/static/422ae4c7db23fc4ac8991e74abec0f5d/b768e/photo-1518818608552-195ed130cdf4.jpg 1350w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1350px) 100vw, 1350px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>High schoolers often have trouble finding a career path. They search for a job that they like and fits their personal and their family's needs. And you can find it too.</p>\n<p>What are the most important methods to locking in your lifelong career path?</p>\n<p>I'll show you (if you're considering software development).</p>\n<p>But why should you trust some university software developer about career paths?</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1706px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/afc5d94e8436374802d6d906fdc7a352/5fada/quento.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.888888888888886%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Quento’s suite of tools helps you streamline your studying like never before.\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/afc5d94e8436374802d6d906fdc7a352/5fada/quento.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/afc5d94e8436374802d6d906fdc7a352/fc2a6/quento.png 450w,\n/static/afc5d94e8436374802d6d906fdc7a352/1cfc2/quento.png 900w,\n/static/afc5d94e8436374802d6d906fdc7a352/5fada/quento.png 1706w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1706px) 100vw, 1706px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Quento’s suite of tools helps you streamline your studying like never before.</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Because I mentor 3 high school robotics teams and 2 high school startups. Check out <a href=\"https://quento.ca\">Quento</a>, whose tools help streamline studying for high school students.\nYou can also check out <a href=\"https://edgeprim.com/\">EdgePrim</a> who creates custom software for small businesses.\nI also recently helped deliver an MVP (more on what that means later) to customers at Ericsson.</p>\n<h2 id=\"my-story\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#my-story\" aria-label=\"my story permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>My story</h2>\n<p>In Grade 11, I wasn't quite sure what I wanted to be. I was deciding between software or radiology. Both seemed cool, so to figure out how one of them was like, I registered into my high school's co-op program.</p>\n<p>Luckily, two of my friends recommended me to a telecom company with over 100 employees. Learning Python and passing the interview in two weeks while studying and writing exams was <em>quite</em> the experience.</p>\n<p>My supervisor, Jonathan Crone, drew and explained the architecture of the product. That diagram was the most influential on my development and growth. More on that later.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3d91684a34164e02bd271458e1909cb3/6951b/work-station-straight-on-view.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"work station straight on view\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/3d91684a34164e02bd271458e1909cb3/d9c39/work-station-straight-on-view.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3d91684a34164e02bd271458e1909cb3/20e5d/work-station-straight-on-view.jpg 450w,\n/static/3d91684a34164e02bd271458e1909cb3/8e1fc/work-station-straight-on-view.jpg 900w,\n/static/3d91684a34164e02bd271458e1909cb3/d9c39/work-station-straight-on-view.jpg 1800w,\n/static/3d91684a34164e02bd271458e1909cb3/6951b/work-station-straight-on-view.jpg 1950w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>When explaining the architecture, I had no clue what he was saying. All I heard were various names, mostly from various mythologies:</p>\n<p>Cassandra, Ares, Hecate, Hyperion, Heimdallr, Levski, Forseti, Helios, Cthulu... Greedo, from Star Wars? Postgres, mod_cluster, Spark, NiFi, ZooKeeper, Solr, Kafka, WildFly, Epiphany, Delorean... Isn't Delorean a car manufacturer? Yeah... I had no clue what was going on...</p>\n<p>Figuring out the meanings behind those names was my last priority during the term. First, I had to figure out how to complete my tasks (called stories).</p>\n<p>It was a constant struggle for the whole 2 months of the term. Turns out that challenges are super fun for me.</p>\n<p>By the end of the term, I had learned Python, pandas, NumPy, matplotlib, Solr querying and ssh. More importantly, I learnt:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>what it's like to work at a real software company and</li>\n<li>that I'd like to continue making software solutions for the rest of my career.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"architecture-diagram\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#architecture-diagram\" aria-label=\"architecture diagram permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Architecture diagram</h2>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1599px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e82f68aa1abad378cd02a169d30df81f/4c7dc/architecture-diagram.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 70.44444444444444%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"A beautified version of the architecture diagram\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/e82f68aa1abad378cd02a169d30df81f/4c7dc/architecture-diagram.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e82f68aa1abad378cd02a169d30df81f/fc2a6/architecture-diagram.png 450w,\n/static/e82f68aa1abad378cd02a169d30df81f/1cfc2/architecture-diagram.png 900w,\n/static/e82f68aa1abad378cd02a169d30df81f/4c7dc/architecture-diagram.png 1599w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1599px) 100vw, 1599px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">A beautified version of the architecture diagram</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>After my term ended, I still had no clue what the names in the architecture diagram meant.</p>\n<p>So I decided to look some of them up.</p>\n<p>I started with Cassandra and that led me down an Apache rabbit hole: Kafka, Hadoop, MapReduce, ZooKeeper, NiFi, Solr, Spark, Avro, Pig and HBase to name a few.</p>\n<p>That led me to figuring out some cool facts. For example, Google File System's (GFS) whitepaper inspired Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS).</p>\n<p>I ended up figuring out that some of those fancy names, like Ares and Hecate were proprietary to the company. Although, a lot of them were open source technologies.</p>\n<p>So what factors led to me locking in my career choice?</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Early mentorship</li>\n<li>Real work experience</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"early-mentorship\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#early-mentorship\" aria-label=\"early mentorship permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Early mentorship</h2>\n<p>On the job, I was constantly challenged, but how was I able to complete the stories assigned to me?</p>\n<p>Jonathan, my mentor and supervisor had a huge backlog of stories to complete, so there were lots of things he could assign to me.</p>\n<p>He was a woodworking teacher, a senior engineer and had a history of mentoring co-ops. As a result, he knew how to tailor the co-op experience to individuals of varying backgrounds.</p>\n<p>Starting at my skill level, these stories became increasingly difficult in complexity. For me it felt as though there was a constant challenge, since I was learning when completing stories.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/624888e0e5752f5f08b4eed1f9e2e32c/6951b/photo-1569098644584-210bcd375b59.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"photo 1569098644584 210bcd375b59\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/624888e0e5752f5f08b4eed1f9e2e32c/d9c39/photo-1569098644584-210bcd375b59.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/624888e0e5752f5f08b4eed1f9e2e32c/20e5d/photo-1569098644584-210bcd375b59.jpg 450w,\n/static/624888e0e5752f5f08b4eed1f9e2e32c/8e1fc/photo-1569098644584-210bcd375b59.jpg 900w,\n/static/624888e0e5752f5f08b4eed1f9e2e32c/d9c39/photo-1569098644584-210bcd375b59.jpg 1800w,\n/static/624888e0e5752f5f08b4eed1f9e2e32c/6951b/photo-1569098644584-210bcd375b59.jpg 1950w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>He assigned me stories that weren't too easy or too difficult.</p>\n<p>He also explained the architecture of the product. My lack of understanding in that area led to me exploring further. That's what got me \"hooked\" on software.</p>\n<p>That's a pretty good indicator that someone loves what they're doing. If I hadn't liked it, my quest of a full understanding wouldn't be there.</p>\n<p>Having a mentor early on can set you on the right path. From there you can become independent and find your own path.</p>\n<h2 id=\"real-work-experience\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#real-work-experience\" aria-label=\"real work experience permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Real work experience</h2>\n<p>Many high schoolers love programming and do a lot of it, but the lack of real work experience shows.</p>\n<p>Their code is generally not production-ready. By this, I mean that you can find <a href=\"https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/\">OWASP Top 10 Security Risks</a> in it. Their apps are not regulatory compliant (<a href=\"https://gdpr.eu/\">GDPR</a>, <a href=\"https://www.priv.gc.ca/en/privacy-topics/privacy-laws-in-canada/the-personal-information-protection-and-electronic-documents-act-pipeda/\">PIPEDA</a>). It's written in a way that's resistant to changing requirements (especially scaling).</p>\n<p>But that's okay.</p>\n<p>High schoolers usually don't need to deal with scaling or lots of users where these pop up. That doesn't mean it's ideal though.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cdeadec9caaf9865173bf4b3b368975b/6951b/photo-1555099962-4199c345e5dd.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"photo 1555099962 4199c345e5dd\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/cdeadec9caaf9865173bf4b3b368975b/d9c39/photo-1555099962-4199c345e5dd.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cdeadec9caaf9865173bf4b3b368975b/20e5d/photo-1555099962-4199c345e5dd.jpg 450w,\n/static/cdeadec9caaf9865173bf4b3b368975b/8e1fc/photo-1555099962-4199c345e5dd.jpg 900w,\n/static/cdeadec9caaf9865173bf4b3b368975b/d9c39/photo-1555099962-4199c345e5dd.jpg 1800w,\n/static/cdeadec9caaf9865173bf4b3b368975b/6951b/photo-1555099962-4199c345e5dd.jpg 1950w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>Minimum viable product (MVP)</strong> refers to a version of a product with a minimal set of features, but just enough to satisfy early customers.</p>\n<p>Let's look at a part of <a href=\"https://discord.com/\">Discord</a>'s company culture:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Build quickly to prove out a product feature, but always with a path to a more robust solution.</p>\n<p>Source: <a href=\"https://blog.discord.com/how-discord-stores-billions-of-messages-7fa6ec7ee4c7\">How Discord Stores Billions of Messages</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>They built an MVP with MongoDB and had plans for switching out (to Cassandra) when performance and stability issues popped up.</p>\n<p>High schoolers are missing the action plan if their product becomes successful.</p>\n<p>Developers can find ways to develop this skill through exposure.</p>\n<p>I'll give my example.</p>\n<p>Although GDPR lawsuits against Facebook, Google and others were on the news, I didn't pay much attention to what it was all about.</p>\n<p>It was when I worked in a company that cared about GDPR-compliance that I realized its importance. The same applies to the other points I mentioned.</p>\n<p>Real work experience provides hands-on, practical knowledge no matter what field.</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-get-real-work-experience-in-high-school\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-to-get-real-work-experience-in-high-school\" aria-label=\"how to get real work experience in high school permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to get real work experience in high school</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f8c1ff3693ccb868757b34a3b99c9ecd/6951b/photo-1517148815978-75f6acaaf32c.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"photo 1517148815978 75f6acaaf32c\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/f8c1ff3693ccb868757b34a3b99c9ecd/d9c39/photo-1517148815978-75f6acaaf32c.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f8c1ff3693ccb868757b34a3b99c9ecd/20e5d/photo-1517148815978-75f6acaaf32c.jpg 450w,\n/static/f8c1ff3693ccb868757b34a3b99c9ecd/8e1fc/photo-1517148815978-75f6acaaf32c.jpg 900w,\n/static/f8c1ff3693ccb868757b34a3b99c9ecd/d9c39/photo-1517148815978-75f6acaaf32c.jpg 1800w,\n/static/f8c1ff3693ccb868757b34a3b99c9ecd/6951b/photo-1517148815978-75f6acaaf32c.jpg 1950w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Finding a job is very hard, especially as a high school student.</p>\n<p>There are companies that have job postings for high school co-op/interns. You'll likely need some alternatives, since there aren't many.</p>\n<p>Reach out to your connections. They can be parents, family friends or even parents of friends . They can find ways to get you into the company and potentially act as your supervisor.</p>\n<p>Additionally, I'd recommend looking at other high schoolers around the city to see if anyone has already found co-ops. If you can find one, you should try reaching out and seeing if you can get a similar opportunity.</p>\n<p>If those people don't exist, the search will be much harder.</p>\n<p>You will likely need to research for companies in your area. Often startups will take high school co-ops, but may be harder to find. You'll need to cold email/message employees at these companies.</p>\n<p>Unfortunately, cold emails don't have high response rates. Don't lose hope though. All you need is one positive reply and you're good.</p>\n<p>Hopefully this helps get you an early start or help you find your career path.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How early mentorship kickstarted my career (in software)","date":"September 06, 2020","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"src":"/static/422ae4c7db23fc4ac8991e74abec0f5d/2244e/photo-1518818608552-195ed130cdf4.jpg"}}}},"excerpt":"High schoolers often have trouble finding a career path. They search for a job that they like and fits their personal and their family's…","timeToRead":4}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/early-mentorship/","previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/zerotwo/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ZEROTWO: Zero Effort Rentals & Off-Chain Transactional Wallet Operations"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3159585216","63159454"],"slicesMap":{}}